         <abstract>
            <p>This paper defines the exposure to currency risk of the prices of financial and physical assets. Exposure is correctly defined as the set of coefficients in a multiple linear regression of the dollar price of an asset on a vector of exchange rates. The Appendix further shows that a hedge in the amount of the exposure, thus defined, both minimizes the variance of the hedged asset and renders the residual variance independent of exchange rates. Implications of these results are discussed in the body of the paper.</p>
         </abstract>
